# LexFlow AI — Core Invariants

Read `.ai/memory/PROJECT.md` and `.ai/memory/INVARIANTS.md` before any implementation.

## Architecture Pipeline

```
Frontend (Next.js) → FastAPI → RabbitMQ → Celery → n8n (private) → External
```

## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. **Business logic in FastAPI** (`services/`) — NEVER in n8n or frontend
2. **n8n is private** — orchestration only; no public access; no PostgreSQL nodes
3. **Frontend never calls n8n** — all via FastAPI REST API
4. **Async AI only** — LLM via Celery worker; API returns 202 Accepted
5. **Matter walls** — unauthorized case access returns **404** (not 403)
6. **Human-in-the-loop** — legal AI outputs require attorney approval
7. **Transactional outbox** — events atomic with DB writes
8. **Immutable audit logs** — append-only for all mutating operations
9. **Case-scoped RAG** — vector search always filters by case_id
10. **No secrets in code** — AWS Secrets Manager only

